Merge pull request #471 from 0xced/find-xcodeproj

Better heuristic for finding the .xcodeproj directory
Update CHANGELOG
Truncate error only when presenting it

Do not skip descendants when searching for .xcodeproj

This is probably premature optimization, so better have smaller code.
Do not assume the .xcodeproj file has the same name as the package

Better error handling

* Define constants for error domains and error codes
* Bubble up errors and present them to the user instead of just logging them
Use NSError for expected error instead of catching exception

Better heuristic for finding the .xcodeproj directory

The "Make the Mac Great Again" plugin would not install because Alcatraz assumes that the .xcodeproj has the exact same name as the package. This may not be true, for example "Make the Mac Great Again" xcodeproj file is "MakeTheMacGreatAgain.xcodeproj" (without the spaces).

This new heuristic searches for all .xcodeproj and works fine if only one exists in the cloned directory.

Merge pull request #465 from 0xced/recursive

Clone git repositories with the --recursive option

Clone git repositories with the --recursive option

Repositories using submodules need to be cloned recursively.

For example, https://github.com/mralexgray/DVTPlugInCompatibilityUUIDifier would fail to build because its AHLaunchCtl submodule was not cloned.

Merge pull request #382 from alcatraz/menu-item-missing-fix

Subscribe to Xcode launch notification synchronously

Subscribe to launch notification synchronously

There seems to be a (common) edge case where the subscription to the
notification would be deferred until after the notification is fired.
This change fixes it by subscribing immediately upon initialization and
then deferring the menu item creation block instead as may be needed.

Merge pull request #155 from haaakon/patch-1

Setting retina build status image for travis ci

Insert menu item before "Bring All to Front"

There's a lot of real estate between that ⇧⌘2 and ⇧⌘9.

For example, Attica[1] uses ⇧⌘8, and because of Xcode plug-in load
order, it's inserted after Alcatraz, yielding a menu that looks like
this:

  Documentation and API Reference  ⇧⌘0
  Welcome to Xcode                 ⇧⌘1
  Organizer                        ⇧⌘2
  Package Manager                  ⇧⌘9
  Snippet Editor                   ⇧⌘8

If we insert the item before the section's separator item, we can cure
my mild case of OCD.

[1]: https://github.com/kattrali/attica

Signed-off-by: Stephen Celis <stephen@stephencelis.com>
